BEGIN_PGML
Remember that a set is just a collection of elements.  Here are two definitions about sets:
a.  A set [`A`] is a subset of a set [`B\text{,}`] written [`A \subseteq B`] provided every element in [`A`] is also an element of [`B\text{.}`]

a.  Given sets [`A`] and [`B\text{,}`] the union of [`A`] and [`B\text{,}`] written [`A \cup B`] is the set containing every element that is in [`A`] or [`B`] or both.

Let's build some examples.

END_PGML

